{"id":"bd-7lgi","title":"verifyServerTarget uses hardcoded root credentials, ignores config","description":"migrate_safety.go:121 verifyServerTarget() opens a MySQL connection with hardcoded DSN 'root@tcp(%s)/' — no password, always user 'root'. However, the Dolt server may be configured with different credentials (via metadata.json or env vars). If the server requires authentication, the verification query will fail even when the actual migration would succeed with the correct credentials.

By contrast, verifyMigrationData() (line 205) correctly accepts user/password parameters from the caller.

Fix: Add user and password parameters to verifyServerTarget() and use them in the DSN. Update callers in runMigrationPhases() to pass the configured credentials.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"steve.yegge@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-01T18:09:13Z","created_by":"beads/polecats/opal","updated_at":"2026-03-01T18:09:13Z"}

