{"id":"bd-mppa","title":"FindOrphanedIssues silently swallows provider errors","description":"In git.go line ~687, when provider.GetOpenIssues(ctx) fails, FindOrphanedIssues returns ([]OrphanIssue{}, nil) — no error. This silently hides database connectivity failures, authentication issues, or other real errors. The caller CheckOrphanedIssues would report 'no orphans' when the check actually could not run.

Also, CheckGitWorkingTree and CheckGitUpstream (lines ~282-293, 383-431) run multiple exec.Command('git', ...) calls without a context timeout. If the git process hangs, the doctor check blocks indefinitely.

Suggested fix: Return the error from GetOpenIssues. Use exec.CommandContext with a timeout for git commands.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"steve.yegge@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-01T18:12:01Z","created_by":"beads/polecats/jasper","updated_at":"2026-03-01T18:12:01Z"}

