{"id":"bd-c1g8","title":"Hardcoded root: credentials in perf_dolt.go bypass configured authentication","description":"In perf_dolt.go line ~108, runDoltServerDiagnostics constructs DSN as 'root:@tcp(...)' ignoring the configured user and BEADS_DOLT_PASSWORD environment variable. Meanwhile, openDoltDB in dolt.go correctly reads user/password from config and environment. If the server has a non-root user or requires a password, the perf diagnostics will fail or connect with wrong credentials.

Additionally, no context timeout is set on diagnostic queries (line ~122 uses bare context.Background()). Queries could hang indefinitely against a slow or deadlocked server. Other functions use context.WithTimeout consistently.

Suggested fix: Use the same credential resolution as openDoltDB. Add context.WithTimeout.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"steve.yegge@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-01T18:10:46Z","created_by":"beads/polecats/jasper","updated_at":"2026-03-01T18:10:46Z"}

